caption.body: Presenting candid snapshots of four of San Francisco's most beloved and iconic neighborhoods, Emily Fromm's mosaic installation "Four Corners" captures the diverse urban beauty of the city in single-moment vignettes. People bustle on streets amidst the unmistakable architecture, signs, and landscapes of the region, creating picturesque memories of each featured neighborhood. The artwork is intended to serve as a visual memento for each viewer, offering a first or departing look into San Francisco for locals and visitors alike.  "Four Corners" by @EmilyLFromm is on view post-security in Harvey Milk Terminal 1.
